law.text:
Each container of vegetable or herb seeds which is sold, offered or exposed for sale, or transported in the State for planting purposes shall bear or have attached in a conspicuous place a plainly written or printed label or tag in the English language, except when the scientific name is the commonly accepted name, giving the following information:
For containers of at least 1 pound --
Lot number or other lot identification;
Name of kind and variety of seed;
Percentage of germination, exclusive of hard seed;
Percentage of hard seed, if present;
The month and year the test was completed to determine the percentages; and
The name and address of the person who labeled the seed or who sells, or offers or exposes the seed for sale in the State.
For containers less than 1 pound --
The name of kind and variety of seed;
The year for which the seed is packaged or the germination percentage and date;
For seed which germinates less than the standard last established by the Secretary under this subtitle:
The name and address of the person who labeled the seed or who sells, offers or exposes the seed for sale in the State.
